🧠 Problem Statement

Given:

a pattern string (e.g. "abba")
a sentence string (e.g. "dog cat cat dog")

👉 Check if the sentence follows the same pattern.

Rules:
Each character maps to one unique word
Each word maps back to one unique character
➡️ This is called a bijection (1–1 mapping)

Example 1
pattern = "abba"
s = "dog cat cat dog"
✔️ true

Example 2
pattern = "abba"
s = "dog cat cat fish"
❌ false


Solution :
class Solution {
    fun wordPattern(pattern: String, s: String): Boolean {
        val words = s.split(" ")
        if(pattern.length != words.size) return false
        val map1 = mutableMapOf<Char,String>()
        val map2 = mutableMapOf<String,Char>()
        for(i in pattern.indices){
            val c1 = pattern[i]
            val c2 = words[i]

            if(map1[c1]?.let{ it != c2} == true) return false
            if(map2[c2]?.let{it != c1} == true) return false
            map1[c1] = c2
            map2[c2] = c1
        }

        return true
    }
}
